The paper presents an algorithmic approach that uses deep convolutional networks to estimate mitotic activity in histopathological images. This involves image analysis and computer vision techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer science sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques, as it involves selecting the image segment with the highest mitotic activity. Lastly, the paper involves multimedia (cs.MM) techniques, as it deals with analyzing and processing images.
